üü¶ US3 ‚Äì Display a persistent action bar with BACK and NEXT / VALIDATE buttons

User Story

As a coach
I want to have permanent BACK and NEXT (or VALIDATE) buttons
So that I can easily navigate between steps and explicitly confirm certain actions when required

‚∏ª

Description

A persistent action bar is displayed above the footer on all steps of the Return Hardware journey.

It contains:
	‚Ä¢	BACK button: navigates to the previous step
	‚Ä¢	NEXT or VALIDATE button:
	‚Ä¢	NEXT is used for standard step-to-step navigation
	‚Ä¢	VALIDATE is used when the current step requires an explicit confirmation action (e.g. validation, submission, confirmation)

Behavior
	‚Ä¢	The label of the primary action button is context-dependent (NEXT or VALIDATE)
	‚Ä¢	Only one primary action button is displayed at a time
	‚Ä¢	The primary button is disabled until the current step is valid
	‚Ä¢	BACK does not reset previously entered data
	‚Ä¢	The action bar is always visible
	‚Ä¢	Header and action bar remain visible during error handling (modal or toast)

‚∏ª

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN I am on a step of the Return Hardware process
THEN a persistent action bar with BACK and a primary action button is visible

WHEN the step is a standard navigation step
THEN the primary button label is "NEXT"

WHEN the step requires explicit confirmation
THEN the primary button label is "VALIDATE"

WHEN the current step is not valid
THEN the primary action button (NEXT or VALIDATE) is disabled

WHEN I click BACK
THEN I return to the previous step
AND previously entered data is preserved

WHEN I click NEXT or VALIDATE
THEN the current step is validated
AND I move to the next step or confirm the action

WHEN an error modal or toast is displayed
THEN the header and action bar remain visible


